 "cells": [
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# 🔍 Step 3: SHAP Explainability Module\n",
    "### Machine Learning-Based Insider Threat Detection System\n",
    "**Savannah Ward | MSIT 5910 Capstone**\n",
    "\n",
    "This notebook adds SHAP (SHapley Additive Explanations) to explain *why* the Isolation Forest flagged specific users.\n",
    "\n",
    "**What you'll get:**\n",
    "- A summary plot showing which features matter most across ALL users\n",
    "- A force plot showing exactly why a specific user (e.g. U0457) was flagged\n",
    "- A waterfall plot for a deep dive into one user's feature contributions\n",
    "- A bar chart of the top features driving anomaly scores globally\n",
    "\n",
    "**Prerequisite:** Run `4ModelTraining.ipynb` first and make sure your feature matrix and fitted Isolation Forest model are saved."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "---\n",
    "## Cell 1: Install and Import SHAP"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Install SHAP (only needs to run once per Colab session)\n",
    "!pip install shap -q\n",
    "\n",
    "import shap\n",
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "import matplotlib\n",
    "from sklearn.ensemble import IsolationForest\n",
    "from google.colab import drive\n",
    "\n",
    "# Mount Google Drive to load saved outputs\n",
    "drive.mount('/content/drive')\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"SHAP version: {shap.__version__}\")\n",
    "print(\"✅ All libraries loaded successfully.\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "---\n",
    "## Cell 2: Load Feature Matrix and Refit Model\n",
    "\n",
    "> **Note:** SHAP needs access to the fitted model object. Since Colab doesn't persist variables between sessions, we reload the feature matrix from Google Drive and refit the Isolation Forest here."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# -----------------------------------------------------------\n",
    "# UPDATE THIS PATH to match where you saved your feature matrix\n",
    "# -----------------------------------------------------------\n",
    "FEATURE_MATRIX_PATH = '/content/drive/MyDrive/insider_threat/data/user_features.csv'\n",
    "RISK_SCORES_PATH    = '/content/drive/MyDrive/insider_threat/data/anomaly_scores.csv'\n",
    "\n",
    "# Load feature matrix (500 users x 17 features)\n",
    "feature_df = pd.read_csv(FEATURE_MATRIX_PATH, index_col="user")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Load risk scores so we can identify high-risk users\n",
    "risk_df = pd.read_csv(RISK_SCORES_PATH, index_col="user")\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"Feature matrix shape: {feature_df.shape}\")\n",
    "print(f\"\\nFeature columns:\")\n",
    "for i, col in enumerate(feature_df.columns, 1):\n",
    "    print(f\"  {i:2}. {col}\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Refit Isolation Forest (same parameters as 4ModelTraining.ipynb)\n",
    "iso_forest = IsolationForest(\n",
    "    n_estimators=200,\n",
    "    contamination=0.05,\n",
    "    random_state=42\n",
    ")\n",
    "iso_forest.fit(feature_df)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"\\n✅ Isolation Forest refitted successfully.\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "---\n",
    "## Cell 3: Compute SHAP Values\n",
    "\n",
    "This is the core step. `TreeExplainer` is optimized for tree-based models like Isolation Forest and computes SHAP values efficiently."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "print(\"Computing SHAP values... (this may take 30-60 seconds)\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# TreeExplainer works natively with Isolation Forest\n",
    "explainer = shap.TreeExplainer(iso_forest)\n",
    "shap_values = explainer.shap_values(feature_df)\n",
    "\n",
    "# shap_values shape: (500 users, 17 features)\n",
    "# Positive SHAP value = pushes toward anomaly\n",
    "# Negative SHAP value = pushes toward normal\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"SHAP values shape: {shap_values.shape}\")\n",
    "print(\"\\n✅ SHAP values computed successfully.\")\n",
    "print(\"\\nQuick check — SHAP values for first user (first 5 features):\")\n",
    "for feat, val in zip(feature_df.columns[:5], shap_values[0][:5]):\n",
    "    direction = '⬆ anomalous' if val > 0 else '⬇ normal'\n",
    "    print(f\"  {feat:40s}: {val:+.4f}  {direction}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "---\n",
    "## Cell 4: Summary Plot — Which Features Matter Most?\n",
    "\n",
    "This plot shows the global importance of each feature across all 500 users.\n",
    "- **X-axis**: SHAP value (impact on anomaly score)\n",
    "- **Color**: Feature value (red = high, blue = low)\n",
    "- **Each dot** = one user"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "plt.figure(figsize=(10, 8))\n",
    "\n",
    "shap.summary_plot(\n",
    "    shap_values,\n",
    "    feature_df,\n",
    "    plot_type='dot',       # 'dot' shows distribution, 'bar' shows mean importance\n",
    "    max_display=17,        # Show all 17 features\n",
    "    show=False\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.title('SHAP Summary Plot — Feature Impact on Anomaly Scores', \n",
    "          fontsize=14, fontweight='bold', pad=15)\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.savefig('/content/drive/MyDrive/insider_threat/shap_summary_plot.png', \n",
    "            dpi=150, bbox_inches='tight')\n",
    "plt.show()\n",
    "print(\"✅ Saved to Google Drive.\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "---\n",
    "## Cell 5: Bar Chart — Top Features by Mean SHAP Value\n",
    "\n",
    "A cleaner view of global feature importance — easier to read in a report or presentation."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Calculate mean absolute SHAP value per feature\n",
    "mean_shap = pd.DataFrame({\n",
    "    'feature': feature_df.columns,\n",
    "    'mean_abs_shap': np.abs(shap_values).mean(axis=0)\n",
    "}).sort_values('mean_abs_shap', ascending=True)\n",
    "\n",
    "fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 8))\n",
    "\n",
    "bars = ax.barh(mean_shap['feature'], mean_shap['mean_abs_shap'],\n",
    "               color='steelblue', edgecolor='white', linewidth=0.5)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Highlight top 5 features\n",
    "top5_features = mean_shap.tail(5)['feature'].values\n",
    "for bar, feat in zip(bars, mean_shap['feature']):\n",
    "    if feat in top5_features:\n",
    "        bar.set_color('#e74c3c')\n",
    "\n",
    "ax.set_xlabel('Mean |SHAP Value| (Average Impact on Anomaly Score)', fontsize=11)\n",
    "ax.set_title('Top Features Driving Anomaly Detection\\n(Red = Top 5 Most Influential)', \n",
    "             fontsize=13, fontweight='bold')\n",
    "ax.spines[['top', 'right']].set_visible(False)\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.savefig('/content/drive/MyDrive/insider_threat/shap_feature_importance.png', \n",
    "            dpi=150, bbox_inches='tight')\n",
    "plt.show()\n",
    "print(\"✅ Saved to Google Drive.\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "---\n",
    "## Cell 6: Waterfall Plot — Why Was a Specific User Flagged?\n",
    "\n",
    "This is the most powerful visualization for analyst use. It shows exactly which features pushed a specific user's score up or down.\n",
    "\n",
    "Change `TARGET_USER` to investigate any user in your dataset."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# -----------------------------------------------------------\n",
    "# Change this to investigate any user\n",
    "# -----------------------------------------------------------\n",
    "TARGET_USER = 'U0457'   # The highest risk user from your model\n",
    "\n",
    "# Get the row index for this user\n",
    "if TARGET_USER not in feature_df.index:\n",
    "    print(f\"❌ User {TARGET_USER} not found. Available users (first 10): {list(feature_df.index[:10])}\")\n",
    "else:\n",
    "    user_idx = feature_df.index.get_loc(TARGET_USER)\n",
    "    user_risk_score = risk_df.loc[TARGET_USER, 'risk_score'] if TARGET_USER in risk_df.index else 'N/A'\n",
    "\n",
    "    print(f\"Generating waterfall plot for {TARGET_USER} (Risk Score: {user_risk_score})...\")\n",
    "\n",
    "    # Build SHAP Explanation object for this user\n",
    "    explanation = shap.Explanation(\n",
    "        values=shap_values[user_idx],\n",
    "        base_values=explainer.expected_value,\n",
    "        data=feature_df.iloc[user_idx].values,\n",
    "        feature_names=feature_df.columns.tolist()\n",
    "    )\n",
    "\n",
    "    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 8))\n",
    "    shap.plots.waterfall(explanation, max_display=17, show=False)\n",
    "    plt.title(f'SHAP Waterfall Plot — {TARGET_USER} (Risk Score: {user_risk_score})',\n",
    "              fontsize=13, fontweight='bold', pad=15)\n",
    "    plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "    plt.savefig(f'/content/drive/MyDrive/insider_threat/shap_waterfall_{TARGET_USER}.png',\n",
    "                dpi=150, bbox_inches='tight')\n",
    "    plt.show()\n",
    "    print(f\"✅ Saved to Google Drive.\")\n",
    "\n",
    "    # Print a plain-language summary\n",
    "    print(f\"\\n📋 Plain-language breakdown for {TARGET_USER}:\")\n",
    "    user_shap = pd.Series(shap_values[user_idx], index=feature_df.columns)\n",
    "    top_drivers = user_shap.abs().sort_values(ascending=False).head(5)\n",
    "    for feat in top_drivers.index:\n",
    "        val = user_shap[feat]\n",
    "        raw = feature_df.loc[TARGET_USER, feat]\n",
    "        direction = 'INCREASED anomaly score' if val > 0 else 'decreased anomaly score'\n",
    "        print(f\"  • {feat}: raw value = {raw:.3f} → {direction} by {abs(val):.4f}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "---\n",
    "## Cell 7: Compare Top 5 High-Risk Users Side by Side\n",
    "\n",
    "This heatmap shows SHAP values for your top flagged users — great for spotting patterns across the high-risk group."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import seaborn as sns\n",
    "\n",
    "# Get top 10 highest risk users\n",
    "TOP_N = 10\n",
    "\n",
    "if 'risk_score' in risk_df.columns:\n",
    "    top_users = risk_df.nlargest(TOP_N, 'risk_score').index.tolist()\n",
    "else:\n",
    "    # Fallback: use raw Isolation Forest scores\n",
    "    raw_scores = iso_forest.decision_function(feature_df)\n",
    "    top_users = feature_df.index[np.argsort(raw_scores)[:TOP_N]].tolist()\n",
    "\n",
    "# Build SHAP value DataFrame for these users\n",
    "top_indices = [feature_df.index.get_loc(u) for u in top_users if u in feature_df.index]\n",
    "shap_top = pd.DataFrame(\n",
    "    shap_values[top_indices],\n",
    "    index=[feature_df.index[i] for i in top_indices],\n",
    "    columns=feature_df.columns\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(14, 6))\n",
    "sns.heatmap(\n",
    "    shap_top.T,\n",
    "    cmap='RdBu_r',\n",
    "    center=0,\n",
    "    annot=True,\n",
    "    fmt='.2f',\n",
    "    linewidths=0.5,\n",
    "    ax=ax,\n",
    "    cbar_kws={'label': 'SHAP Value (red = pushes toward anomaly)'}\n",
    ")\n",
    "ax.set_title(f'SHAP Values — Top {TOP_N} Highest Risk Users', \n",
    "             fontsize=13, fontweight='bold', pad=15)\n",
    "ax.set_xlabel('User ID', fontsize=11)\n",
    "ax.set_ylabel('Feature', fontsize=11)\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.savefig('/content/drive/MyDrive/insider_threat/shap_top_users_heatmap.png',\n",
    "            dpi=150, bbox_inches='tight')\n",
    "plt.show()\n",
    "print(\"✅ Saved to Google Drive.\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "---\n",
    "## 📚 What You Learned\n",
    "\n",
    "| Visualization | What it tells you |\n",
    "|---|---|\n",
    "| **Summary Plot** | Which features most consistently drive anomaly scores across all users |\n",
    "| **Feature Importance Bar Chart** | Clean ranking of the 17 features by global impact |\n",
    "| **Waterfall Plot** | Exactly why one specific user was flagged — feature by feature |\n",
    "| **Top Users Heatmap** | Whether high-risk users share common behavioral patterns |\n",
    "\n",
    "### Key SHAP Concepts to Remember\n",
    "- **Positive SHAP value** → pushes the user toward being anomalous\n",
    "- **Negative SHAP value** → pushes the user toward being normal\n",
    "- **Base value** → the average model output across all users (the starting point)\n",
    "- **Final prediction** = base value + sum of all SHAP values for that user\n",
    "\n",
    "### Next Steps\n",
    "- Try changing `TARGET_USER` in Cell 6 to compare different high-risk users\n",
    "- Look at the heatmap — do high-risk users share the same red features, or do they each have unique patterns?\n",
    "- Consider adding SHAP output as a column in your risk scores CSV for analyst reporting"
   ]
  }
